1 AN ACT concerning
2 Baltimore City and Takoma Park – Stop Sign Monitoring Systems –
3 Authorization
4 FOR the purpose of authorizing the use of stop sign monitoring systems in school zones in
5 Baltimore City and the City of Takoma Park under the pilot program authorized for
6 Prince George’s County, if authorized by local law; providing that the owner or driver
7 of a motor vehicle recorded failing to obey a stop sign is subject to a citation and a
8 certain civil penalty under certain circumstances; establishing certain defenses to a
9 charge of an alleged violation recorded by a stop sign monitoring system; prohibiting
10 a contractor administering a stop sign monitoring system from being compensated
11 in a certain manner; and generally relating to the use of stop sign monitoring
12 systems in Baltimore City and the City of Takoma Park.
